### Health check
GET http://localhost:8080/health

### Create user (upsert by email)
POST http://localhost:8080/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "google_id": "google-oauth2|1234567890",
  "email": "alice@example.com"
}

### Get user by ID
GET http://localhost:8080/users/123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000

### Get activities for a user (includes aggregations)
GET http://localhost:8080/users/123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000/activities

### Get a single activity with its GPS track
GET http://localhost:8080/activities/123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174001

### Get track points for an activity
GET http://localhost:8080/trackpoints/123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174001

### Upload activity files (CSV + GPX)
# cardioActivities.csv contains the activity list; each .gpx file corresponds
# to the GPS track for one activity (matched by filename in gps_file column).
POST http://localhost:8080/upload?user_id=123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="files"; filename="cardioActivities.csv"
Content-Type: text/csv

<full CSV file contents here>
--boundary--

### OpenAPI / Swagger UI
GET http://localhost:8080/swagger-ui/
GET http://localhost:8080/api-docs/openapi.json
